    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Stiff Systems with CVODE BDF\n\nStiff ODEs contain dynamics on vastly different time scales. Explicit methods (Adams) need tiny time steps to remain stable, while implicit methods (BDF) can take much larger steps.\n\nCVODE's BDF method with dense direct linear solver is well-suited for moderate-dimensional stiff systems.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"numerics-sundials\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 1,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. Van der Pol Oscillator\n\nThe Van der Pol oscillator becomes increasingly stiff as $\\mu$ grows:\n$$\\ddot{x} - \\mu(1 - x^2)\\dot{x} + x = 0$$\n\nWritten as a system: $\\dot{x} = y$, $\\dot{y} = \\mu(1-x^2)y - x$.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Moderate stiffness: mu = 10 */\nmu : 10$\ntspan1 : np_linspace(0.0, 60.0, 5000)$\n\nres1 : np_cvode([y, mu*(1 - x^2)*y - x],\n                [t, x, y], [2.0, 0.0], tspan1,\n                1e-8, 1e-8, bdf)$\n\nt1 : np_slice(res1, all, 0)$\nx1 : np_slice(res1, all, 1)$\ny1 : np_slice(res1, all, 2)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 2,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=\"#2563eb\", line_width=1.5,\n  lines(t1, x1),\n  title=printf(false, \"Van der Pol Oscillator (mu=~d)\", mu),\n  xlabel=\"t\", ylabel=\"x\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": [
        {
